-- Spain’s Diesel, Gasoline Demand Decline in December, Cores Says
-- B y   K o n s t a n t i n   R o z h n o v
-- 2013-01-31T10:04:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-31/spain-s-diesel-gasoline-demand-decline-in-december-cores-says.html
Spain ’s  diesel  consumption dropped
8.6 percent in December, according to Corporacion de Reservas
Estrategicas de Productos Petroliferos, or Cores.  Consumption fell to 1.67 million metric tons last month,
according to preliminary  data  posted today on the government
agency’s website. Gasoline use decreased 8.3 percent to 399,000
tons, the data show.  The drop in consumption for both fuels was the biggest
since September, compared with the same month a year ago, the
data show.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Konstantin Rozhnov in  London  at 
